145typedef struct
146{
147 union
148 {
149 uint8_t MR0; //Mode register 0
150
151 struct
152 {
153 uint8_t DS : 2; //[0..1] drive strength | 00=Full(25 ohm), 01=Half(50 ohm) default, | volatile
154 // | 10=Quarter(100 ohm), 11=Octuple (200 ohm) |
155 uint8_t RLC : 3; //[2..4] Read latency code. | 000 = LC:3, LCx2:6, 33MHz | volatile
156 // | 001 = LC:4, LCx2:8, 66MHz |
157 // | 010 = LC:5, LCx2:10, 109MHz (default) |
158 // | 011 = LC:6, LCx2:12, 133MHz |
159 // | 100 = LC:7, LCx2:14, 166MHz |
160 // | 101 = LC:8, LCx2:16, 200MHz |
161 // | 110 = LC:9, LCx2:18, 200MHz |
162 uint8_t LT : 1; //[5..5] Latency type | 0=Variable(default), 1=Fixed | volatile
163 uint8_t : 1;
164 uint8_t TSO : 1; //[7..7] Temperature Sensor Override | 0=self control refresh, 1=force refresh rate set by MR4.RFR | volatile
165 }MR0_b;
166 } ;
167
168 union
169 {
170 uint8_t MR1; //Mode register 1
171
172 struct
173 {
174 uint8_t VID : 5; //[0..4] Vendor ID | 5'b01101 | non-volatile
175 uint8_t : 2;
176 uint8_t ULP : 1; //[7..7] Half sleep. | 0=no half sleep, 1=half sleep supported | non-volatile
177 }MR1_b;
178 } ;
179
180 union
181 {
182 uint8_t MR2; //Mode register 2
183
184 struct
185 {
186 uint8_t DENSITY : 3; //[0..2] Density | | non-volatile
187 uint8_t GENERATION : 2; //[3..4] Generation |
188 uint8_t GBD : 3; //[5..7] Good or bad die | others=bad, 3'b110=pass | non-volatile
189 }MR2_b;
190 } ;
191
192 union
193 {
194 uint8_t MR3; //Mode register 3
195
196 struct
197 {
198 uint8_t : 4;
199 uint8_t SRF : 2; //[4..5] Self refresh flag | 00=0.5x refresh, 01=1x refresh, 10=4x refresh | non-volatile
200 uint8_t : 1;
201 uint8_t RBXen : 1; //[7..7] Row Boundary Crossing Enable | 0=not supported, 1=supported | non-volatile
202 }MR3_b;
203 } ;
204
205 union
206 {
207 uint8_t MR4; //Mode register 4
208
209 struct
210 {
211 uint8_t PASR : 3; //[0..2] control refresh address space | 0~7=different address space. default 0=full array | volatile
212 uint8_t RFS : 2; //[3..4] Refresh Frequency setting | x0=always 4x(default), | volatile
213 // | 1=enable 1x when temperature allows,
214 // | 3=enable 0.5x when temperature allows,
215 uint8_t WLC : 3; //[5..7] Write latency code. | 000 = LC:3, 33MHz | volatile
216 // | 100 = LC:4, 33MHz
217 // | 010 = LC:5, 66MHz
218 // | 110 = LC:6, 109MHz (default)
219 // | 001 = LC:7, 133MHz
220 // | 101 = LC:8, 166MHz
221 // | 011 = LC:9, 200MHz
222 // | 111 = LC:10, 200MHz
223 }MR4_b;
224 } ;
225
226 union
227 {
228 uint8_t MR6; //Mode register 6
229
230 struct
231 {
232 uint8_t ULPM : 8; //[0..7] ULP modes | 0xF0=Half slepp, 0xC0=Deep power down | volatile
233 }MR6_b;
234 } ;
235
236 union
237 {
238 uint8_t MR8; //Mode register 8
239
240 struct
241 {
242 uint8_t BL : 2; //[0..1] Burst Length | 0~4=16B,32B,64B,2KB wrap | volatile
243 uint8_t BT : 1; //[2..2] Burst type | 0=normal, 1=hybrid
244 uint8_t RBX : 1; //[3..3] Row Boundary Crossing Read EN | 0=Reads stay within 1K, 1=Reads cross 1K boundray | volatile
245 uint8_t : 2;
246 uint8_t IOM : 1; //[6..6] IO mode | 0=octal default, 1=hex
247 uint8_t : 1;
248 }MR8_b;
249 } ;
250}am_devices_mspi_psram_aps25616ba_regs_t;

697//
698// This function runs approximately 200+ns on the 96MHz clock
699//
700// That results in the steps being 1us/32 ~= 31.25ns per step (96MHz Clock)
701// 1us/64 ~= 15.625ns per step (192MHz clock)
702//
703
704//*****************************************************************************
714//*****************************************************************************
715
716#if (defined (__ARMCC_VERSION)) && (__ARMCC_VERSION < 6000000)
717extern __asm void APS25616BA_tXPHS_delay( uint32_t ui32Iterations );
718#elif (defined (__ARMCC_VERSION)) && (__ARMCC_VERSION >= 6000000)
719extern __attribute__((always_inline)) void APS25616BA_tXPHS_delay( uint32_t ui32Iterations );
720#elif defined(__GNUC_STDC_INLINE__)
721extern __attribute__((naked)) void APS25616BA_tXPHS_delay( uint32_t ui32Iterations );
722#elif defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
723#pragma diag_suppress = Pe940 // Suppress IAR compiler warning about missing
724 // return statement on a non-void function
725extern __stackless inline void APS25616BA_tXPHS_delay( uint32_t ui32Iterations );
726#pragma diag_default = Pe940 // Restore IAR compiler warning
727#else
728#error Compiler is unknown, please contact Ambiq support team
729#endif
